<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-11T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="1763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1763">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 810.00/145.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to
                            Guatemala</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-11T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>When you have received the telegram of January 10, 2 p.m., from the
                            American Minister to Salvador, you will immediately take up this matter
                            with the President of Guatemala, vigorously impressing upon him the
                            absolute necessity of putting a stop to this hostile movement against
                            Salvador, in utter disregard of the Washington conventions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>